Below is one systematic way to interpret and rebuild the scene exactly as shown, without rotating any dictionary blocks.  I have broken the solution into three parts per your instructions.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1) ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Total Block Count:  13  
  –  Main “double‐arch” structure uses 11 blocks  
  –  The smaller separate arch‐and‐roof structure uses 2 blocks  
• Layering (3 layers total):
  1) Bottom Layer:
     – Two red arches (forming the front of the main structure)  
     – One red arch in the smaller separate piece  
     – One tall green rectangular block behind the arches  
     – Two tall yellow rectangular blocks behind the green block  
  2) Middle Layer:
     – One blue cube on top of the left arch  
     – One orange cube/block on top of the right arch  
     – Two yellow half‐cylinder pieces spanning between left and right arch  
     – One orange roof wedge on the small separate arch  
  3) Top Layer:
     – Two orange roof wedges, each perched atop its tower (one over the blue cube, one over the orange cube)

Spatially:
• The two front arches sit side by side.  
• The blue cube sits directly above the left arch; the orange cube sits above the right arch.  
• Two yellow half‐cylinders bridge the gap between the tops of those two cubes.  
• A tall green block and two tall yellow blocks stand behind the arches, rising up in the rear.  
• Off to the right, a single red arch has an orange roof wedge placed on top, forming the small separate structure.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2) SELECTING THE REQUIRED DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below are the blocks (by index) that match color, shape, and orientation exactly as seen in the target.  Note that some blocks appear multiple times.

• Red arches (3 total):
  – #1 (twice) – used for the left arch in the main structure and for the separate arch
  – #2 (once) – used for the right arch in the main structure
• Blue cube (1 total):
  – #4
• Orange cube/block (1 total):
  – #5
• Tall green rectangular block (1 total):
  – #7
• Tall yellow rectangular blocks (2 total):
  – #9 (twice)
• Yellow half‐cylinders (2 total):
  – #12 (twice)
• Orange wedge “roof” pieces (3 total):
  – #15 (three times)

In total, that yields 13 blocks:  
  #1 × 2, #2 × 1, #4 × 1, #5 × 1, #7 × 1, #9 × 2, #12 × 2, #15 × 3.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3) STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{  
   Step1:  Move block with index 1   (place left red arch of main structure)  
   Step2:  Move block with index 2   (place right red arch of main structure)  
   Step3:  Move block with index 1   (place red arch for the separate small structure)  
   Step4:  Move block with index 7   (stand the tall green block behind the arches)  
   Step5:  Move block with index 9   (first tall yellow block behind green)  
   Step6:  Move block with index 9   (second tall yellow block behind green)  
   Step7:  Move block with index 4   (place blue cube on top of left arch)  
   Step8:  Move block with index 5   (place orange cube on top of right arch)  
   Step9:  Move block with index 12  (first half‐cylinder bridging tops of arches)  
   Step10: Move block with index 12  (second half‐cylinder bridging tops of arches)  
   Step11: Move block with index 15  (roof wedge on the small separate arch)  
   Step12: Move block with index 15  (roof wedge on top of the blue cube)  
   Step13: Move block with index 15  (roof wedge on top of the orange cube)  
}  

Following these steps with the listed blocks (without rotating them further) reproduces the target scene exactly as shown.
